RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 15400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRETTY RENA ran off pace from the leaders then had a strong drive on the outside in the middle of the turn to take the lead and slightly drew off from the pack. ANDREABANANAS ran in the middle of the pack then started to make their bid after the sixteenth pole to end up in place. GONE KAT ran at the back of the pack then had a late kick to pass foes down the middle of the track. STAY BY THE BEACH ran evenly throughout in the middle of the pack had a slight gain very late in the race. BURNINGDAYLIGHT pressed the pace early on then coming down the stretch hung and shuffled back slightly. SNOOZY SUZY ran at the back of the pack then took an outside path to pass weakened foes. REALLY A STORM had good early speed then slowed the remainder of the race. ICY REBEL ran at the back of the pack with no advance managed to pass a tired foe on the stretch. SHE'S ALL ATTITUDE set the early pace with their pace getting pressed by BURNINGDAYLIGHT then they faded hard at the start of the stretch. THIS RACE IS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 16200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Cl aiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RATIONAL D'ORO ran off pace from the leaders then assumed command at the three eights pole then drew off coming on to the stretch. GREATEST GLORY ran at the back of the pack then took an outside path accompanied with a strong kick to pass foes late into the race. BODIE'SLITTLEGIRL ran in the middle of the track then had slight bid after the sixteenth pole pass a fading foe. ZIPPIN BY U ran at the back of the pack then starting at the three eights pole they started to make a bid on the outside. REAL ME ran evenly with a slight gain mid race the hung late stretch to get passed late stretch. HEAR ME ROAR set the early pace then faded around the three eights and quarter pole then proceeded with a steady pace thru the wire. PREMEDITATED LILY ran in the middle of the pack but coming onto the stretch shuffled back slightly getting passed by a couple foes. RAPPERS THIEF ran off pace then started to fade at the start of the stretch, just ended up running out of gas. LAS TRES MARIPOSAS ran in the middle of the pack and just didnt have the gas left to continue with the pace set by the main pack as they pulled away. DOUBLE STORM started off in the middle of the pack on the rail, they just got outran throughout the race. THIS RACE IS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 16200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2022 - 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Pr ice $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FABSTRACTION ran with a steady gain in pace throughout the race eventually passing all of their foes. GOLDEN BAND ran with an even pace with slight bursts of speed periodically thru the race. SHARP WARNING had good early speed, set the initial pace then was passed by the three eights pole but maintained a comfortable pace off pace from the leaders. LOTTA GUSTO ran at the back of the pack then changed leads and started to gain and overtaking foes. REINING PESOS ran in the middle of the pack with a slight gain in pace towards mid stretch. MAJORWAYHOME came out of the gate in the front of the pack but continued to shuffle back as the race progressed. CYCLONE MESA ran at the front of the pack was in the lead for about a third of the race then approaching the wire faded hard. SMOOTH BLUES ran with a steady pace at the back of the pack had a slight advance around the three eights pole. OMACHE KID ran evenly throughout the race eventually passing a single foe late into the stretch. CAJUN FIRE ran in the middle of the pack but it just was their night as they slowed throughout the race. THIS RACE IS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 87. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 24500. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $12,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 20 Allowed 3 lbs. Cla iming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I'MAGAMBLER ran in the middle of the pack with a slight gain started making a move to the two path on the turn then coming onto the stretch started the final closing drive to the wire and took the lead late into the race. CLUE had good early speed, dropped back slightly to reserve energy for the stretch, then started the bid for the finish at the end of the turn to overtake the foes in front and continued to barrel down the stretch getting caught late, just missing the win. HENRY ON THE RUN ran at the back of the pack then coming out of the turn took to the outside where they followed CLUE partially down the stretch then drifting in slightly before the wire. OFFENSIVE was off slow at the break, then conserved energy for the stretch coming out in the seven path and with a massive rally on the outside overtook many foes. SPINNING BLACK had early speed then slowed slightly but coming on to the stretch took to the rail with a strong rally in the last hundred yards to finish out the race strong. RYDERS UP ran at the front of the pack but started to shuffle back mid way thru the turn. BLACK EYED BANDIT set the early pace then but was wore out by foes by time they reached the late stretch. DECK HUMOR pressed the pace early on then coming on to the stretch gave it all but faded late stretch. SIMPLY ELEMENTARY made a slight bid on the back stretch but that was all they had as they ran out of gas at the end of the turn and start of the stretch fading back to last. THIS RACE IS HAND TIMED.
